The Light, exhausted from its frantic burning, accepted. It slowed its pulse and spread its glow evenly across the stars and the sun. The Darkness wrapped around planets and hid behind mountains, giving form to the Light’s brilliance. Now, every shadow cast by a tree and every cycle of night following day is the result of their truce: the Darkness defining the edges so that the Light may truly be seen.

Write your own myth. Use your previous myth as inspiration, but adapt it in your own way.
Write 200 words. Format exactly:
Myth: [your story here].

